FUNCTION get_form_description( ip_flow_code IN VARCHAR2, ip_stage_code IN VARCHAR2, ip_pid IN NUMBER, ip_id IN NUMBER ) return varchar2 is lv_viewname varchar2(100); lv_description clob; lv_sqlstmt varchar2(4000); begin lv_viewname := get_flow_view_name (ip_flow_code); lv_sqlstmt := 'select description from ' || lv_viewname ||' where process_instance_id = '||ip_pid ||' and instance_id = '||ip_id||' and rownum = 1'; execute immediate lv_sqlstmt into lv_description ; return lv_description; EXCEPTION WHEN NO_DATA_FOUND then RETURN NULL; end get_form_description;

GET_FIRST_STAGE_USERS   (MS_DMS_INLINE_EMAIL_UTILITIES body)
function GET_FLOW_VIEW_NAME (PC_FLOW_CODE varchar2, pc_view_type varchar2 default 'V' ) RETURN VARCHAR2 IS lc_namespace VARCHAR2 (100) := 'xmlns="http://www.metricstream.com/appstudio/mdf"'; lv_flow XMLTYPE; lv_view_name varchar2 (400); begin dbms_output.put_line('2'); SELECT XMLTYPE (flow_xml) INTO lv_flow FROM ms_apps_mdf_flow_xml where flow_code = pc_flow_code; dbms_output.put_line('1'); if pc_view_type='V' then dbms_output.put_line('Anil-inside if'); SELECT stages.EXTRACT ('stage/view/text()', lc_namespace).getstringval() view_name INTO lv_view_name FROM TABLE (XMLSEQUENCE ((SELECT lv_flow.EXTRACT ('process/stages/stage[enabled="Y"]', lc_namespace ) FROM DUAL) ) ) stages WHERE ROWNUM = 1; else dbms_output.put_line('Anil-inside else'); SELECT stages.EXTRACT ('stage/displayview/text()', lc_namespace).getstringval() view_name INTO lv_view_name FROM TABLE (XMLSEQUENCE ((SELECT lv_flow.EXTRACT ('process/stages/stage[enabled="Y"]', lc_namespace ) FROM DUAL) ) ) stages WHERE ROWNUM = 1; end if; dbms_output.put_line('Anil-End : ' || lv_view_name); RETURN lv_view_name; EXCEPTION WHEN NO_DATA_FOUND then return null; end get_flow_view_name;

GET_MULTIROW_ID   (MS_DMS_FLOW_UTILITIES body)
function get_policy_assignment_users( ip_flow_code IN VARCHAR2, ip_stage_code IN VARCHAR2, ip_pid IN NUMBER, ip_id IN NUMBER ) return varchar2 is x_user_list varchar2(4000); x_err_seq number; begin begin ms_apps_mdf_errors_pkg.insert_log (pn_error_handle_id => ip_pid, pn_error_sequence => x_err_seq, pc_error_type => 'LOG', pc_error_text => ' ' || 'ms_dms_flow_utilities.get_policy_assignment_users (' || ' ip_flow_code => ''' || ip_flow_code ||''' ,' || ' ip_stage_code => ''' || ip_stage_code ||''' ,' || ' ip_pid => ' || ip_pid ||' ,' || ' ip_id => ' || ip_id ||' ) ' ); SELECT wm_concat(M.user_group_users) into x_user_list FROM ms_dms_manage_policy_v M WHERE M.process_instance_id =ip_pid AND M.instance_id = ip_id ; SELECT wm_concat(user_name) into x_user_list FROM( SELECT DISTINCT COLUMN_VALUE AS USER_NAME FROM TABLE (ms_apps_utilities.parse_string ( x_user_list , ',' ) ) ) ; exception when others then ms_apps_mdf_errors_pkg.insert_log (pn_error_handle_id => ip_pid, pn_error_sequence => x_err_seq, pc_error_type => 'LOG', pc_error_text => 'DMS x_user_list:' ||x_user_list ); end; return x_user_list; end; function get_policy_assignment_count( ip_flow_code IN VARCHAR2, ip_stage_code IN VARCHAR2, ip_pid IN NUMBER, ip_id IN NUMBER) return number is x_err_seq number; cnt number; begin ms_apps_mdf_errors_pkg.insert_log (pn_error_handle_id => ip_pid, pn_error_sequence => x_err_seq, pc_error_type => 'LOG', pc_error_text => ' ' || 'ms_dms_flow_utilities.get_policy_assignment_users (' || ' ip_flow_code => ''' || ip_flow_code ||''' ,' || ' ip_stage_code => ''' || ip_stage_code ||''' ,' || ' ip_pid => ' || ip_pid ||' ,' || ' ip_id => ' || ip_id ||' ) ' || SQLCODE || '-' || SUBSTR (SQLERRM, 1, 255) ); select count(1) into cnt from si_event_assignments where infolet_id=( SELECT metric_id FROM si_metrics_t WHERE UPPER (metric_name) = UPPER ('MS_DMS_MANAGE_POLICY') ) and process_instance_id=ip_pid ; ms_apps_mdf_errors_pkg.insert_log (pn_error_handle_id => ip_pid, pn_error_sequence => x_err_seq, pc_error_type => 'LOG', pc_error_text => ' ' || 'ms_dms_flow_utilities.get_policy_assignment_users ' || 'return value cnt = ''' || cnt ); return cnt; return 100; end;

--user id x_flowstatus number :=2; x_latestflag varchar2(100):='Y'; xn_error_handle_id Number:=ip_pid; xn_error_sequence Number:=1000; xn_error_code varchar2(1000); x_sql varchar2(4000); Begin x_created_by_id := ip_user_id; PRODUCTION_EMAIL   (MS_DMS_INLINE_EMAIL_UTILITIES body)
FUNCTION author_publish_assign(IP_FLOW_CODE IN VARCHAR2, IP_STAGE_CODE IN VARCHAR2, IP_PID IN NUMBER, ip_id in number) RETURN CLOB AS L_USERNAME_LIST CLOB; X_LENGTH NUMBER; X_ERR VARCHAR2(4000); CURSOR V_USERS IS SELECT DISTINCT L1_APPROVER_SEC "USERS" FROM MS_DMS_INLINE_CREATE_DOCMUN_V WHERE PROCESS_INSTANCE_ID = IP_PID AND MULTIROW_REGION_ID = MS_DMS_FLOW_UTILITIES.GET_MULTIROW_ID('MS_DMS_INLINE_CREATE_DOCMUNENT', 'SEC') AND instance_id = (SELECT MAX(instance_id) from MS_DMS_INLINE_CREATE_DOCMUN_V where process_instance_id = ip_pid) AND review_response_sec <> 'NRP' UNION SELECT DISTINCT L1_APPROVER_SUB "USERS" FROM MS_DMS_INLINE_CREATE_DOCMUN_V WHERE PROCESS_INSTANCE_ID = IP_PID AND MULTIROW_REGION_ID = MS_DMS_FLOW_UTILITIES.GET_MULTIROW_ID('MS_DMS_INLINE_CREATE_DOCMUNENT', 'SUB') AND instance_id = (SELECT MAX(instance_id) from MS_DMS_INLINE_CREATE_DOCMUN_V where process_instance_id = ip_pid) AND review_response_sec <> 'NRP' UNION SELECT DISTINCT L2_APPROVER_SEC "USERS" FROM MS_DMS_INLINE_CREATE_DOCMUN_V WHERE PROCESS_INSTANCE_ID = IP_PID AND MULTIROW_REGION_ID = MS_DMS_FLOW_UTILITIES.GET_MULTIROW_ID('MS_DMS_INLINE_CREATE_DOCMUNENT', 'SEC') AND instance_id = (SELECT MAX(instance_id) from MS_DMS_INLINE_CREATE_DOCMUN_V WHERE process_instance_id = IP_PID) and upper(requires_approval_from_sec) = '2' AND review_response_sec <> 'NRP' UNION SELECT DISTINCT L2_APPROVER_SUB "USERS" FROM MS_DMS_INLINE_CREATE_DOCMUN_V WHERE PROCESS_INSTANCE_ID = IP_PID AND MULTIROW_REGION_ID = MS_DMS_FLOW_UTILITIES.GET_MULTIROW_ID('MS_DMS_INLINE_CREATE_DOCMUNENT', 'SUB') AND instance_id = (SELECT MAX(instance_id) from MS_DMS_INLINE_CREATE_DOCMUN_V WHERE process_instance_id = IP_PID) and upper(requires_approval_from_sub) = '2' AND review_response_sec <> 'NRP' UNION SELECT DISTINCT L3_APPROVER_SEC "USERS" FROM MS_DMS_INLINE_CREATE_DOCMUN_V WHERE PROCESS_INSTANCE_ID = IP_PID AND MULTIROW_REGION_ID = MS_DMS_FLOW_UTILITIES.GET_MULTIROW_ID('MS_DMS_INLINE_CREATE_DOCMUNENT', 'SEC') AND instance_id = (SELECT MAX(instance_id) from MS_DMS_INLINE_CREATE_DOCMUN_V WHERE process_instance_id = IP_PID) and upper(requires_approval_from_sec) = '2' AND review_response_sec <> 'NRP' UNION SELECT DISTINCT L2_APPROVER_SUB "USERS" FROM MS_DMS_INLINE_CREATE_DOCMUN_V WHERE PROCESS_INSTANCE_ID = IP_PID AND MULTIROW_REGION_ID = MS_DMS_FLOW_UTILITIES.GET_MULTIROW_ID('MS_DMS_INLINE_CREATE_DOCMUNENT', 'SUB') AND instance_id = (SELECT MAX(instance_id) from MS_DMS_INLINE_CREATE_DOCMUN_V WHERE process_instance_id = IP_PID) and upper(requires_approval_from_sub) = '2' AND review_response_sec <> 'NRP'; BEGIN FOR I IN V_USERS LOOP IF I.USERS IS NOT NULL THEN L_USERNAME_LIST := L_USERNAME_LIST || ',' || I.USERS; END IF; END LOOP; x_LENGTH := dbms_lob.getlength(L_USERNAME_LIST); L_USERNAME_LIST := DBMS_LOB.SUBSTR(L_USERNAME_LIST, X_LENGTH, 2); RETURN L_USERNAME_LIST; EXCEPTION WHEN OTHERS THEN return null; END author_publish_assign;

VAL_LIFECYCLE   (MS_DMS_SV_TEST)
=========================================================================== PROCEDURE NAME: VAL_LIFECYCLE DESCRIPTION: PERFORMS THE FOLLOWING VALIDATION: 1.
